ionByID` (doctor command)\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` (line 743)\\n\\n`CondenseSessionByID` calls `CondenseSession` without a specific commit context. When commit hashes aren't available, fall back to the current go-git tree walk (or skip non-agent attribution). This is a salvage path, not performance-critical.\\n\\n### 5. Update tests\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_attribution_test.go`\\n\\n- Update `CalculateAttributionWithAccumulated` call sites for new signature\\n- `TestGetAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees` (line 777) — delete (function removed)\\n- `TestCalculateAttributionWithAccumulated_UserEditsNonAgentFile` (line 697) — key test, update to pass commit hashes; may need a real git repo fixture instead of in-memory trees for the non-agent file detection path\\n\\n**New file:** `cmd/entire/cli/gitops/diff_test.go`\\n- Test `DiffTreeFiles` with a real git repo (create temp repo, make commits, verify output)\\n- Test initial commit (no parent) case\\n- Test multi-commit range\\n\\n### 6. Remove dead code\\n\\n- Delete `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees` from `manual_commit_attribution.go`\\n- Delete `TestGetAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees` from test file\\n\\n### 7. Remove timing instrumentation\\n\\nRemove the timing `logging.Info` calls added during investigation from:\\n- `manual_commit_hooks.go` — PrepareCommitMsg and PostCommit timing logs\\n- `manual_commit_condensation.go` — CondenseSession timing logs\\n\\n## Files Modified\\n\\n- **`cmd/entire/cli/gitops/diff.go`** (new) — `DiffTreeFiles` using `git diff-tree`\\n- **`cmd/entire/cli/gitops/diff_test.go`** (new) — tests for above\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — update `filesChangedInCommit` + remove timing logs\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_attribution.go` — new params, remove `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees`\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — thread commit hashes through opts + remove timing logs\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_attribution_test.go` — update tests\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n2. Build binary, test on rust repo (~58k files): `time git commit -m 'test'` — expect <500ms\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alex/.claude/projects/-Users-alex-workspace-cli--worktrees-3/86a4c45c-4c6f-441c-9e41-80eb453d2c7d.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"7a026f30-249e-4fd3-94a1-4236232487d0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T00:24:55.731Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Fix: Commit Hook Performance (O(n) Tree Walks)\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nPost-commit hook takes **5.4s** on large repos (~58k files). Two hotspots, both doing expensive tree comparisons via go-git when `git diff-tree` does the same thing in ~30ms:\\n\\n| Hotspot | Current | With `git diff-tree` | Where |\\n|---|---|---|---|\\n| `filesChangedInCommit` | 703ms | 25ms | PostCommit, HEAD~1→HEAD |\\n| `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees` | 4,685ms | 36ms | Attribution, AttributionBaseCommit→HEAD |\\n\\n**Note:** `getAllChangedFilesBetweenTrees` intentionally compares `AttributionBaseCommit→HEAD` (not HEAD~1→HEAD) to capture user edits from any manual commits made between condensations. This range must be preserved.\\n\\n**Expected improvement: 5.4s → ~200ms.**\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Create `cmd/entire/cli/gitops/` package\\n\\nNew leaf package for git CLI operations. Start with two functions:\\n\\n**`gitops/diff.go`:**\\n- `DiffTreeFiles(ctx context.Context, commit1, commit2 string) (map[string]struct{}, error)` — runs `git diff-tree --no-commit-id -r -z <commit1> <commit2>`, parses null-separated output, returns set of changed file paths. For initial commits (empty commit1), use `git diff-tree --root -r -z <commit2>`.\\n- `DiffTreeFileList(ctx context.Context, commit1, commit2 string) ([]string, error)` — same but returns `[]string